  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently above the 6550 flip in PIN regime with spot at 6576.7, putting them in active selling mode as they hedge their long gamma positions - the massive 363.8% GEX surge indicates heavy options flow just hit the market creating these stabilizing walls. With spot sandwiched between the 6570 (+12.2B) and 6580 (+15.2B) gamma walls, expect choppy mean-reverting action as dealers will aggressively sell any push toward 6580 and provide support on dips back to 6570. Key inflection remains the 6550 flip - any break below flips dealers to NEX mode where they'd accelerate selling, but the dense positive gamma structure above suggests strong magnetic pull keeping price rangebound between 6570-6580.",
